         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">South-Yarra, ¶ Vic. ¶  ¶ 25/8/92. ¶ T. R. Wilson Esqr ¶ Under Secretary. ¶ Sir. ¶  ¶ In acknowledgement of your telephonic message of the evening of the 23th inst., I have the honor to report, that Mr...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">92.08.25</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Thomas Wilson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">T92/8908, unit 710, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Office, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">South-Yarra,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Vic.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>25/8/92.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">T. R. Wilson Esqr</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Under Secretary.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In acknowledgement of your telephonic message of the evening of the 23th inst., I have the honor to report, that Mr Minchin and Mr French waited yesterday on Dr Dick, who regarded Mr French as not physically strong enough to undertake Warders duties in the Asylum for the Insane. As regards Mr Minchin the positions vacant in the Asylum are less salaried than his, but I presume, that some compensation would be granted him, were he transferred to any position with less Salary than that he has in this establishment. I anticipate, that Dr Dick will report to you directly about these two officers as regards fitness for transfer to the Asylum-Services.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 16 July 1892, Wilson sent a memorandum with two questions to his colleague in the Chief Secretary's Department, J. Killen: '1. How long are Minchin &amp; French provided for on Estimates?' and '2. When were the P.S.Bd asked to [provide] places for them?' Killen returned the memorandum with the answers 3 months' and '3/3/92' respectively.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>There is<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a further note (by Wilson?): 'see [...] re Minchin'.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 30 July, Wilson minuted: 'Write to Govt Botanist to ask that Minchin &amp; French (the two retained<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to 30 Sept) wait on Captn Evans on a day named (see Mr Connor) for examn as to their fitness for employment in that Branch', and this was done in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>T. Wilson to M, 3 August 1892.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 20 August, Wilson asked: 'What result?' The answer, in an unknown hand, dated 22 August, was: 'Both Minchin and French are considered unsuitable as Penal Warders'. A further note, dated 23 August, reads: 'These men were directed by Telephone to call on Dr Dick on 24.8.92'.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The file also contains a further minute, in an unknown hand, that appears to sum up the state of affairs. It is dated 9 September and is further annotated<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>with responses,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in another unknown hand; these<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>responses<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>are given in round brackets:</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>'<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <hi rend="underline">re Minchin &amp; French U.S.</hi>
                        </seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[Under Secretary]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <hi rend="underline">says</hi>
                        </seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>He thinks they have been already reported to the Bd [Board] as available for transfer.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Is it so? (Yes.)</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If so on what date? (15.7.92)</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>What is Dr. Dick's report about them? (Not suitable)</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Number &amp; date of his report. (8.9.92 from Mr Killen)</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>(Capt. Evans says neither will suit him. 22.8.92.) [<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">These brackets are in the minute.</seg>]</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We cannot keep either man permanently Has Minchin passed clerical exam? (No) Or non Cl.? [non Clerical] (No.)</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>(<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <hi rend="underline">US. thinks he has passed neither.</hi>
                        </seg>) [<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">These brackets are in the minute.</seg>]</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <hi rend="underline">Keep them provided for on Estimates</hi>
                        </seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(Noted.) and if necessary write to P.S.B. [Public Service Board] again about them before making that provision (Not necessary)'.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Dr Dick's assessment is amplified in a note in an unknown hand: 'Dr Dick says (8.9.92) that he considers Minchin and French<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <hi rend="underline">unsuitable</hi>
                        </seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for the position of Warders in a Lunatic Asylum'. And Wilson's opinion is given in an unknown hand: 'U.S says (14.9.92) hold this and see that provision is made on Additional Estimates'.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>also M to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>A. McLean, 26 September 1892,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and M to T. Wilson, 7 December<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1892 (in this edition as 92-12-07a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir, your obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
